## CONTEXT TRACKER (MANDATORY)

> Every session carries a **CTX score** (0–280). When CTX ≥ 180 the agent MUST warn. When CTX ≥ 250 the agent MUST run `/end` autonomously.

| Zone | CTX | Action |
|------|-----|--------|
| 🟢 SAFE | 0–100 | Continue normally |
| 🟡 WARN | 101–180 | Wrap up subtask, plan /end |
| 🔴 HIGH | 181–250 | Start /end soon — commit + handoff |
| ⛔ CRITICAL | 251–280 | Execute /end NOW, then ask user to open new chat |

- **Agent:** `bun agent:run context_tracker --dry` — run anytime, mandatory before long multi-step tasks
- **Auto-trigger rule:** If the agent detects CTX ≥ 250 it MUST emit `/end` without waiting for user prompt
- **Score factors:** uncommitted files × 4, session commits × 2, changed code files × 1, handoff size (KB) × 0.5, agent runs × 8

