## INCIDENTAL FINDINGS PROTOCOL (2026-04-08 — MANDATORY)

When you encounter something broken/improvable while working on a different task:

| Severity | Action |
|----------|--------|
| **CRITICAL** — security hole, data loss, exposed key, production broken | Fix immediately, same commit |
| **HIGH** — type error, broken test, drift, dead code blocking current work | Fix if <30min, else P0 task |
| **MODERATE** — code smell, naming, missing test, doc mismatch | Create P1 task with file:line, continue |
| **LOW** — style, minor refactor, aspirational | Add `LEARNING:` in next commit, no task |

**Rule:** Never stop mid-task for LOW severity. Never create tasks for trivial items. Fix CRITICAL immediately — never defer.

**Task format:** `- [ ] **PREFIX-NNN [P0]**: description — found while working on X. File: path:line.`

