## MULTI-IDE SYNC RULES (2026-04-08 — MANDATORY)

> This file (`.windsurfrules`) IS the canonical project rules file.
> Claude Code reads `CLAUDE.md` (repo) as adapter. Global rules in `~/.claude/CLAUDE.md`.
> **Rule of truth:** when `.windsurfrules` and `CLAUDE.md` diverge, `.windsurfrules` wins for project rules.

### TASKS.md EDIT PROTOCOL (prevents data loss in multi-window/multi-agent envs)
1. **COMMIT TASKS.md IMMEDIATELY** after any edit — do not defer. Parallel agents/windows WILL run `git restore` during their commits and silently lose your uncommitted changes.
2. **git add TASKS.md && git commit** BEFORE spawning any background agents that may commit.
3. **Background agents MUST NOT run** `git restore .`, `git checkout .`, `git reset --hard`, or `git clean -f`. Only commit specific files they authored.
4. **When working alongside another open IDE window:** always `git pull --rebase` before editing TASKS.md, then commit within 2 minutes of editing.

### PARALLEL AGENT GIT SAFETY
- Agents MUST `git add <specific-files-only>` — NEVER `git add -A` or `git add .`
- Before any agent commit: `git stash list` to detect in-progress work from other sessions
- If stash entries exist: warn user before committing ("⚠️ uncommitted changes from another session detected")
- Agents MUST NOT touch `.husky/`, `.guarani/`, `TASKS.md` unless their task explicitly requires it

### GOVERNANCE SYNC RULE
- Key numeric limits (TASKS.md max lines, AGENTS.md max lines) MUST match across:
  - `.windsurfrules` (this file)
  - `.husky/pre-commit` (enforcement)
  - `CLAUDE.md` (repo adapter)
- When changing a limit: update ALL THREE files in the SAME commit. Divergence = governance debt.
- `scripts/governance-sync.sh` validates consistency. Run it before any governance commit.
